---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import paulAjesImage from "../assets/paul-ajes.png";
---

<section>
  <h2 class="bold-2xl">Webhooks and beyond</h2>
  <p class="regular-l sans-serif manifesto-text">
    Over the last decade, webhooks have become the go-to mechanism for
    delivering platform events. While transformative, they suffer from
    well-known limitations.
    <br />
    <br />
    Best practices today often dictate validating and queuing webhooks via a message
    bus upon receipt. This raises a fundamental question: <strong
      class="regular-l sans-serif"
      >Why rely on the inefficiency of a public HTTP endpoint at all? Why not
      deliver events directly to a secure, efficient destination?</strong
    >
    <br />
    <br />
    We believe the industry must evolve beyond the limitations of webhooks. <strong
      class="regular-l sans-serif"
      >The future of event delivery lies in interoperable, secure, and efficient
      Event Destinations.</strong
    > By embracing this pattern, we can build a developer experience that drives
    progress and simplifies event-driven architectures for everyone.
  </p>
  <img src="/images/signature.svg" alt="Outpost Manifesto" />

  <div class="divider">
    <span class="dots dots-left"></span>
    <span class="dots dots-right"></span>
  </div>

  <p class="regular-l quote">
    "I've been working with (and often against) webhooks for years, both as a
    consumer and an implementer, always wishing that we as an industry could
    come up with something better. In my opinion, Event Destinations are exactly
    that."
  </p>
  <div class="quote-author">
    <Image src={paulAjesImage} alt="Paul Asjes" />
    <div class="quote-author-text">
      <span class="bold-m">Paul Asjes</span>
      <br />
      <span class="regular-m">Developer Experience Engineer @ ElevenLabs</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <a
    class="button monospace"
    href="https://eventdestinations.org"
    target="_blank">Event Destinations Initiative -></a
  >
</section>

<style>
  section {
    margin-top: 200px;
    margin-bottom: 200px;
    max-width: 600px;
    box-sizing: unset;

    @media (max-width: 744px) {
      margin-top: 100px;
      margin-bottom: 100px;
    }
  }

  .divider {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background-color: var(--outline-neutral);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-14);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-14);
  }

  .quote {
    color: var(--foreground-neutral);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-8);
  }

  .button {
    text-align: center;
    display: block;
    text-transform: none;
    padding-top: var(--spacing-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-4);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .quote-author {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--spacing-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-15);
    .regular-m {
      color: var(--foreground-neutral-2);
    }

    img {
      width: 48px;
      height: 48px;
    }
  }

  .manifesto-text {
    color: var(--foreground-neutral-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-10);
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--foreground-neutral);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
